  </xml><p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Day 2 : Trek from&nbsp; Rola Khuli camp to Bhirgu lake
summit and back to Rola Kholi</b></p>

<p class="MsoNormalM">&nbsp;<b>Trek Distance – 10</b>&nbsp;km – 7/8 Hours journey</p>

<p class="MsoNormalM">&nbsp;<b>Mode of the journey –&nbsp;</b>On foot</p>

<p class="MsoNormalM">&nbsp;<b>Altitude – Bhrigu lakes summit&nbsp;</b>&nbsp;–
14,009 feet</p>

<p class="MsoNormalM">&nbsp;<b>Night Stay –&nbsp;</b>Our Campsite – on a
twin-shared basis</p>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>7:00 AM: Wake Up and Breakfast</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Start
     Your Day:</b>&nbsp;Wake up early to enjoy the serene morning at Rola
     Kholi.</li>
 <li><b>Breakfast:</b>&nbsp;Have
     a hearty breakfast to fuel your trek. Typical options may include oatmeal,
     eggs, bread, fruits, and tea/coffee.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>8:00 AM: Start Trek to Bhrigu Lake Summit</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Trek
     Distance:</b>&nbsp;Approximately 6 km one way to Bhrigu Lake.</li>
 <li><b>Altitude:</b>&nbsp;Bhrigu
     Lake is situated at an altitude of about 4,300 meters (14,100 feet).</li>
 <li><b>Trek
     Duration:</b>&nbsp;Around 3-4 hours to reach the summit, depending on your
     pace and fitness level.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>8:30 AM: Begin Trekking</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Trail
     Description:</b>&nbsp;The trek starts with a gradual ascent through
     meadows and forests. As you gain altitude, the trail becomes steeper.</li>
 <li><b>Scenic
     Views:</b>&nbsp;Enjoy stunning views of the surrounding peaks, valleys,
     and the lush green landscape.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>10:30 AM: Reach Bhrigu Lake Summit</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>At
     the Lake:</b>&nbsp;Take time to explore the beautiful Bhrigu Lake, known
     for its stunning blue waters and serene environment. This high-altitude
     lake is often surrounded by snow, even in summer.</li>
 <li><b>Photography:</b>&nbsp;Capture
     the breathtaking views and take plenty of pictures. The lake is considered
     sacred, so remember to respect the surroundings.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>11:30 AM: Relax at the Lake</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Snack
     Break:</b>&nbsp;Enjoy some light snacks or packed lunch near the lake.</li>
 <li><b>Rest
     and Hydration:</b>&nbsp;Hydrate and rest while taking in the majestic
     views.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>12:30 PM: Begin Return Trek to Rola Kholi Base Camp</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Trek
     Duration:</b>&nbsp;Approximately 2-3 hours back.</li>
 <li><b>Descent:</b>&nbsp;The
     return trek will be easier and quicker, but be cautious on the descent.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>3:00 PM: Arrive Back at Rola Kholi Base Camp</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Rest:</b>&nbsp;Take
     some time to relax and enjoy the surroundings at the camp.</li>
 <li><b>Lunch:</b>&nbsp;Have
     a warm lunch prepared by your guides.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Afternoon Activities:</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Exploration:</b>&nbsp;You
     can explore nearby meadows or relax at the camp.</li>
 <li><b>Photography:</b>&nbsp;Capture
     the beautiful landscape and perhaps some candid moments with your trekking
     group.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Evening:</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Dinner
     Preparation:</b>&nbsp;Enjoy another delicious meal in the evening.</li>
 <li><b>Campfire:</b>&nbsp;Gather
     around the campfire for stories, songs, and camaraderie under the starlit
     sky.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Overnight Stay:</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Accommodation:</b>&nbsp;Stay
     overnight in tents at Rola Kholi Base Camp.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Important Tips:</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Altitude
     Acclimatization:</b>&nbsp;Pay attention to how you feel at higher
     altitudes. Take breaks as needed, and communicate with your guides if you
     experience any discomfort.</li>
 <li><b>Trekking
     Gear:</b>&nbsp;Ensure you have appropriate clothing, trekking poles, and a
     daypack with water and snacks for the ascent.</li>
 <li><b>Weather
     Conditions:</b>&nbsp;Be prepared for changing weather conditions; carry a
     windbreaker and rain gear if necessary.</li>
</ul>


