  </xml><p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Day 3: Trek from Rola Khuli to Gulaba Road head (06 km)
(3/4 Hours) same day drive to Manali Reach evening 4:30 pm</b></p>

<p class="MsoNormalM">&nbsp;<b>Trek + Road Distance –&nbsp;</b>28 km – 5/6 Hours
journey</p>

<p class="MsoNormalM">&nbsp;<b>Mode of the journey –&nbsp;</b>By taxi 22 km – On
foot 06 km</p>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>7:00 AM: Wake Up and Breakfast</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Start
     Your Day:</b>&nbsp;Enjoy a leisurely morning at Rola Kholi.</li>
 <li><b>Breakfast:</b>&nbsp;Fuel
     up with a nutritious breakfast, such as porridge, fruits, and tea/coffee.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>8:00 AM: Pack Up and Prepare for Departure</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Tents
     and Gear:</b>&nbsp;Pack your belongings and ensure that all camping
     equipment is ready for transport.</li>
 <li><b>Final
     Check:</b>&nbsp;Make sure to collect all personal items and leave no trace
     behind.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>8:30 AM: Start Trek to Gulaba Road Head</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Trek
     Distance:</b>&nbsp;Approximately 6 km.</li>
 <li><b>Trek
     Duration:</b>&nbsp;About 3-4 hours, depending on your pace.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Trekking Details:</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Trail
     Description:</b>&nbsp;The trail back to Gulaba Road Head is generally
     downhill, making the trek easier than the ascent. Expect scenic views of
     the mountains and valleys as you descend.</li>
 <li><b>Flora
     and Fauna:</b>&nbsp;Keep an eye out for local wildlife and enjoy the lush
     surroundings, especially if you trek during the spring or summer months
     when flowers bloom.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>12:30 PM: Arrival at Gulaba Road Head</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Lunch:</b>&nbsp;You
     may have a packed lunch at the road head or snacks, depending on your
     trekking schedule.</li>
 <li><b>Rest:</b>&nbsp;Take
     some time to relax and enjoy the views before your drive back.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>1:30 PM: Drive from Gulaba Road Head to Manali</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Travel
     Mode:</b>&nbsp;Private vehicle.</li>
 <li><b>Distance:</b>&nbsp;Approximately
     24 km.</li>
 <li><b>Estimated
     Travel Time:</b>&nbsp;About 1 hour.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>2:30 PM: Departure from Gulaba Road Head</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Scenic
     Drive:</b>&nbsp;The drive back to Manali offers beautiful views of the
     valleys and hills. Enjoy the picturesque landscape along the way.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>3:30 PM: Arrival in Manali</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Explore
     Manali:</b>&nbsp;Depending on your interest and time, you may explore the
     local markets or grab a bite to eat before concluding your trek.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>4:30 PM: End of Trek</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Return:</b>&nbsp;The
     trek officially concludes around this time. Say goodbye to your guides and
     fellow trekkers.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Important Tips:</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Hydration:</b>&nbsp;Ensure
     you drink plenty of water throughout the trek and during the drive back.</li>
 <li><b>Check
     Your Gear:</b>&nbsp;Double-check that you have all your belongings before
     leaving the campsite.</li>
 <li><b>Weather
     Awareness:</b>&nbsp;Keep an eye on the weather conditions during your
     descent, as they can change rapidly in the mountains.</li>
</ul>

<p class="MsoNormalM"><b>Scenic Viewpoints on the Route:</b></p>

<ul type="discd">
 <li><b>Gulaba
     Road Head Area:</b>&nbsp;Known for its lush greenery, stunning mountain
     views, and alpine meadows, the area around Gulaba Road Head offers several
     picturesque spots for photos.</li>
 <li><b>En
     Route to Manali:</b>&nbsp;The road from Gulaba to Manali will have various
     scenic points where you can stop and enjoy the natural beauty of the
     Himalayas.</li></ul></p>                           </div>
